Neat! By the way you don't have to keep making seperate variables if you use objects e.g.
``````````
    var candleX1 = 244;
    var candleY1 = 142;
    var candleX2 = 272;
    var candleY2 = 162;
    var candleX3 = 300;
    var candleY3 = 142;

`````````
becomes
`````````
var candle = {
    left: {
      x: 244,
      y: 244,
    },
    middle: {
    x: 272,
    y: 162
    },
    right:{
    x: 300,
    y: 142
    },
};

then you can call the variables like this.

candles.left.x
`````````

Hope this helps you! :D

